All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable
public class BlockOk
extends GroupEvent

Event used to notify the blocking of the group, prior to a view change.
When a layer receives the BlockOk it is notified that a view change is necessary. Any layer can hold the BlockOk for a period of time to do some necessary operations. But when it resends the BlockOk it agrees not to send any GroupSendableEvent until the new View is delivered.
The restriction is not mandatory, but failure to inforce it may cause unpredictable behavior.

Version:
0.1
Author:
Alexandre Pinto
